Use QMainWindow of the QtWidgets to create a main application window.

You can use the QMainWindow to add some new content on it.

You can use the QMainWindow as a subclass to add new content on it.

When you subclass a Qt class you must always call the super
__init__ function to allow Qt to set up the object.

You can go to http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/widget-classes.html#basic-widget-classes to find out some new widget ideas and how to implement them.



Use the QSize to handle the size of the application.
Use the setFixedSize() to set the fixed size.
Use the setMinimumSize() to set the minimum size
Use the setMaximumSize() to set the maximum size